\begin_layout Subsection
Operation of the FlowCAM using a 50 um Flow cell
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
For processing samples within 15-20 min using a 20x objective and 50 µm
 flowcell:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Shorten the length of the tubing between the funnel and the flow cell as
 much as possible (~1cm).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
If possible use a smaller funnel with a narrow base (less overall volume
 – one possible idea would be to cut the top end of a disposable plastic
 pipet that has a very narrow stem diameter).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Add the sample and set the pump to PRIME.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Once the sample has reached the flow cell, process the sample using autotrigger
 mode for the necessary period of time (~5-10 mins).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Once the run has finished, remove excess sample in the funnel with a pipet
 (disposable), add and rinse funnel with filtered seawater.
 Have the pump set to prime.
 Rinse funnel with filtered seawater and continue to remove fluid from the
 funnel while the pump is priming with a pipet – continue for 30 seconds
 until FSW has entered the 50 µm depth flow cell.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Remove the FSW from the funnel to the neck of the funnel.
 Add your next sample and prime the pump once again until the sample has
 entered the flow cell (monitor using setup and focus), then begin to run
 the next sample.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
With a 5-10 min run using autotrigger, and these rinsing techniques the
 processing time of each sample should be approximately 15-20 minutes.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Chapter
Computer control of scientific devices
